data.enText: a person who has been trained in the science of animal medicine, whose job is to treat animals who are sick or injured
the place where a vet works

data.chText: 明天我得把狗带到兽医诊所去诊治。
data.enText: I've got to take the dog to the vet's tomorrow.

data.chText: 审查（某人过去的生活和职业）
data.enText: to find out about a person's past life and career in order to decide if they are suitable for a particular job

data.chText: 由于安全的缘故，所有的求职申请人都要经过严格的审查。
data.enText: All candidates are carefully vetted for security reasons.

data.chText: 仔细检查，审查（内容、质量等）
data.enText: to check the contents, quality, etc. of sth carefully

data.chText: 所有报道都要经过仔细检查后才能发表。
data.enText: All reports are vetted before publication.

means: 审查(某人过去的生活和职业)
仔细检查，审查(内容、质量等)

tr: a person who has served in the armed forces
a doctor who practices veterinary medicine

example: Someone should vet this report before it goes out
She vetted for the farms in the area for many years

value.def: A vet is someone who is qualified to treat sick or injured animals.

value.boxr_value: in AM, usually use 美国英语通常用 veterinarian

value.def: A vet is someone who has served in the armed forces of their country, especially during a war.

example.ex: The New England Shelter in Boston will serve Christmas dinner for 200 vets...
example.tran: 波士顿的新英格兰收容所将为200名老兵提供圣诞晚餐。

value.def: If something is vetted, it is checked carefully to make sure that it is acceptable to people in authority.

example.ex: He can find no trace of a rule requiring research to be vetted before publication...
example.tran: 他找不到任何要求研究成果在发表前需经审查的规定。

example.ex: All objects are vetted by a distinguished panel of experts...
example.tran: 所有物品都交由一个著名的专家小组检查鉴定。

example.ex: He had not been allowed to read any book until his mother had vetted it.
example.tran: 未经母亲的审查，他什么书也不能看。

value.def: If someone is vetted, they are investigated fully before being given a particular job, role, or position, especially one which involves military or political secrets.

example.ex: She was secretly vetted before she ever undertook any work for me...
example.tran: 她在为我工作以前曾受到过秘密考查。

example.ex: People who marry into the Royal Family will have to be vetted much more carefully in future.
example.tran: 那些与皇室成员结婚的人未来将受到更细致的调查。

value.tran: （尤指对将要从事涉及军事或政治机密工作人员的）调查，审查，考查

example.ex: The government is to make major changes to the procedure for carrying out security vetting.
example.tran: 政府将对安全检查的执行程序作出重大调整。
